            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p>Additional data sources used on this site include the <a href="https://boe.franklincountyohio.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Franklin County Board of Elections</a> (election results), the <a href="https://www.columbus.gov/Government/City-Council" target="_blank" rel="noopener">City of Columbus</a> (council member directory and committee assignments), and <a href="https://cbusareacommissions.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cbusareacommissions.org</a> (area commission directory).</p>
  </section>

  {/* ================================================================ */}
  {/* SECTION: Data Pipeline (3D.5 continued)                          */}
  {/* ================================================================ */}
  <section id="pipeline" class="data-section">
    <h2>Data Pipeline</h2>
    <p>The demographic data on this site is produced by a reproducible pipeline of Python scripts maintained in the project's <code>/scripts/</code> directory:</p>
    <p><strong><code>build_district_profiles.py</code></strong> pulls ACS 5-Year estimates from the Census Bureau API, maps block groups to council districts using the city's official crosswalk file, computes population-weighted aggregations for each district, and writes the results to the district JSON files that power this site.</p>
    <p><strong><code>compare_sources.py</code></strong> reads the ACS-derived district data and the Esri current-year estimates side by side, computes percentage variances for every metric, flags outliers for review, and produces the variance analysis documented in <code>data_notes.md</code>.</p>
    <p>Both scripts and their documentation are available in the project's <a href="https://github.com/tfulton/columbusdistricts-site/tree/main/scripts" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><code>/scripts/</code> directory on GitHub</a>.</p>
    <p>Found an error or have a data correction? Use the <strong>Suggest an Edit</strong> form on any <a href="/districts/district-one/">district page</a>, or reach out to the team at <a href="https://www.theconfluencecast.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Confluence Cast</a>.</p>
  </section>

